157438", "dc:description": "The clique-chromatic number of a graph G, \u03c7c(G), is the least number of colors on V (G) without a monocolored maximal clique of size at least two. If G is triangle-free, \u03c7c(G) = \u03c7(G); we then consider only graphs with a triangle. Unlike the chromatic number, the clique-chromatic number of a graph is not necessary to be at least those of its subgraphs. Thus, for any family of graphs F, the boundedness of {\u03c7c(G)|G F} has been investigated. Many families of graphs are proved to have a bounded set of clique-chromatic numbers. In literature, only few families of graphs are shown to have an unbounded set of clique-chromatic numbers, for instance, the family of line graphs. This paper gives another family of graphs with such an unbounded set. These graphs are obtained by the well-known Mycielski's construction with a certain property of the initial graph.", "prism:coverDate": "2015-12-01", "prism:aggregationType": "Journal", "prism:url": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/abstract/scopus_id/85073157438", "subtypeDescription": "Article", "dc:creator": {"author": [{"ce:given-name": "Tanawat", "preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "Tanawat", "ce:initials": "T.", "ce:surname": "Wichianpaisarn", "ce:indexed-name": "Wichianpaisarn T."}, "@seq": "1", "ce:initials": "T.", "@_fa": "true", "affiliation": {"@id": "60103462", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/affiliation/affiliation_id/60103462"}, "ce:surname": "Wichianpaisarn", "@auid": "56447073400", "author-url": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/author/author_id/56447073400", "ce:indexed-name": "Wichianpaisarn T."}]}, "link": [{"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "self", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/abstract/scopus_id/85073157438"}, {"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "scopus", "@href": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85073157438&origin=inward"}, {"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "scopus-citedby", "@href": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/citedby.uri?partnerID=HzOx